.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a basic command-line interpreter written in C. 
It executes commands entered by the user in interactive or non-interactive mode.

It supports the following features:
.TP
- Executing commands by absolute path or using the PATH environment variable
.TP
- Handling command arguments
.TP
- Built-in commands: exit, env
.TP
- Proper exit status codes: 0, 1, 2, 127
.TP
- Memory-safe execution without leaks
.SH USAGE
Run the shell:
.RS
$ ./simple_shell
.RE
Enter commands at the prompt:
.RS
$ ls -l
$ /bin/pwd
$ exit
.RE
Non-interactive usage:
.RS
$ echo "ls -l" | ./simple_shell
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns:
.TP
0  if the command was successful
.TP
1  for a general error (fork failure)
.TP
2  for misuse of commands (invalid arguments)
.TP
127  if the command was not found
.SH AUTHOR
